Not everyone needs (or wants) a £1,000+ premium EV charger. If you just want to charge your car overnight on a cheap tariff without spending a fortune on hardware, a budget charger makes a lot of sense — especially when the OZEV grant can knock up to £350 off the installed price.

But "budget" doesn't have to mean "rubbish." The best affordable chargers in 2026 still deliver 7.4kW charging, app control, and smart scheduling. You'll sacrifice some features compared to premium models, but the core job — charging your EV overnight for cheap — gets done just as well.

We've compared the three best budget EV chargers available in the UK right now: the **Ohme ePod**, **Rolec WallPod**, and **EO Mini Pro 3**. Here's which one to buy and what you're giving up.

